st: @@PLACEHOLDER@@ ne a robetse ho lora ka cavern ea Arrakeen, batho ba khutsitseng bohle ba mo potileng ba tsamaea leseling le lefifi la glowglobes. E ne e le hantle, e ne e le ho tšoana le cathedral ha a ntse a utloa molumo o fokolang oa metsi a tsoang metsing. Le ha a ntse a lula torong, @@PLACEHOLDER@@ o ne a tseba hore o tla e hopola ha a tsoha. O ne a lula a hopola litoro tse boletsoeng esale pele.

en_masked: @@PLACEHOLDER@@ fell asleep to dream of an Arrakeen cavern, silent people all around him moving in the dim light of glowglobes. It was solemn there and like a cathedral as he listened to a faint sound—the drip-drip-drip of water. Even while he remained in the dream, @@PLACEHOLDER@@ knew he would remember it upon awakening. He always remembered the dreams that were predictions.
